<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{9}{y}={82}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{3}{x}+{4}{y}={32}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({8},{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -3. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{3}}{{8}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{3}}}{{8}}{\left({8}{x}+{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{3}}}{{8}}{\left({82}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({3}\right)}{x}+-{3.375}{y}=-{30.75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}+{4}{y}={32}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.625}{y}={1.25}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{1.25}}{{0.625}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{9}{\left({2}\right)}={82}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left({18}\right)}={82}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={82}-{\left({18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={64}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{64}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({8},{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

